[1
Date: Wed, 08 Sep 1999 09:33:59 -0400
From: Michael McElvaine <MMCELVAINE@mailoce.oce.usda.gov>

In your [CHC's response about stagnant swimming pools, you questioned
whether this was true [and why. Most of the eastern United States has
been suffering from drought conditions. The recent heavy rains from
Hurricane Dennis have only improved the situation slightly.
Until this week, we had drought emergency conditions in the
Virginia/Maryland/DC area which called for severe restrictions in the use
of water. One of these restrictions was a ban on topping out swimming
pools. When the water level gets too low, the recirculating pumps cannot
operate. Stagnant swimming pools were common in our area until the ban was
lifted this week. This may also be the case in the NYC area.
--
Michael D. McElvaine
e-mail: <MMCELVAINE@mailoce.oce.usda.gov>
[Very informative. Read more below. - Mod.CHC
