[2
Date: Wed, 8 Sep 1999 10:42:58 -0400
From: Carl J. Mitchell <cjm2@cdc.gov>

Neglected swimming pools in urban areas definitely can be a major source of
_Culex pipiens_ complex mosquitoes (the probable vectors of the SLE
outbreak in NY). Such mosquito production was a major problem in affluent
neighborhoods of Orange County, California, as far back as the early 1970's.
--
Carl J. Mitchell, Sc.D.
Supervisory Research Entomologist
Division of Vector-Borne Infectious Diseases
Centers for Disease Control
P.O. Box 2087
Fort Collins, Colorado 80522
e-mail: cjm2@cdc.gov
