[3
Date: Wed, 08 Sep 1999 06:00:49 -0700
From: William K. Reisen <arbo@lightspeed.net>

Most likely the _Aedes_ and _Anopheles_ are not important vectors of SLE
virus,
because they rarely feed on birds. More important is _Culex pipiens pipiens_,
the species probably responsible for [SLE virus transmission in New York.
--
Bill Reisen
UC Davis
e-mail: <arbo@lightspeed.net>
